counts <- read.csv("GSE89633_counts.tsv", row.names=1, sep="\t")
conditions <- read.csv("GSE89633_conditions.tsv", row.names=1, sep="\t")
dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = counts,
                              colData = conditions,
                              design = ~ conditions + cells)
dds <- DESeq(dds)
vst_dds <- vst(dds)
counts.norm <- assay(vst_dds)

plotPCA(vst_dds, intgroup=c("conditions", "cells")) + theme_bw()

max_8000 <- names(rev(sort(rowSums(counts(dds))))[1:8000]) # ะฝะฐะทะฒะฐะฝะธั 8000 ัะธะปัะฝะพ ัะบัะฟัะตััะธัะพะฒะฐะฝัั ะณะตะฝะพะฒ
dds_new <- dds[rownames(dds) %in% max_8000,] # ะพััะฐะฒะปัะตะผ ัะพะปัะบะพ ััะธ 8000 ัะธะปัะฝะพ ััะฟัะตััะธัะพะฒะฐะฝะฝัั ะณะตะฝะพะฒ

dds_new_log <- rlog(dds_new)
## -- note: fitType='parametric', but the dispersion trend was not well captured by the
##    function: y = a/x + b, and a local regression fit was automatically substituted.
##    specify fitType='local' or 'mean' to avoid this message next time.
dds_new_log_a <- assay(dds_new_log)
clustering <- Kmeans(dds_new_log_a, 6, method="correlation", iter.max=20000)
conditions[, 1] #
##  [1] cell type: FAP cell type: FAP cell type: FB  cell type: FB  cell type: FAP cell type: FAP cell type: SMP
##  [8] cell type: FB  cell type: FB  cell type: FAP cell type: FAP cell type: SMP cell type: FB  cell type: FB 
## [15] cell type: FAP cell type: FAP cell type: SMP cell type: SMP cell type: FB  cell type: FB 
## Levels: cell type: FAP cell type: FB cell type: SMP
conditions[, 2] # 
##  [1] condition: DKO condition: WT  condition: DKO condition: WT  condition: DKO condition: WT  condition: DKO
##  [8] condition: DKO condition: WT  condition: DKO condition: WT  condition: WT  condition: DKO condition: WT 
## [15] condition: DKO condition: WT  condition: DKO condition: WT  condition: DKO condition: WT 
## Levels: condition: DKO condition: WT
sort_clust <- sort(clustering$cluster)
to_visualise <- dds_new_log_a[names(sort_clust),
                            order(conditions[, 2],conditions[, 1])] 

to_visualise <- t(apply(to_visualise, 1, function(r) {
  (r - min(r)) / (max(r) - min(r))
}))

m <- as.data.frame(sort_clust)
m$sort_clust <- as.factor(m$sort_clust)


pheatmap(to_visualise, 
         show_rownames =F, cluster_rows = F,
         cluster_cols=F,
         annotation_col = conditions, annotation_row = m)
